1
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,750
Attendees at a conference shouldn't need to check their phones

2
00:00:09,050 --> 00:00:11,050
to know what's on next.

3
00:00:11,350 --> 00:00:15,100
They should be able to look up at a screen

4
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:17,650
and see exactly what's happening now,

5
00:00:17,950 --> 00:00:20,575
what's coming up, and where it is.

6
00:00:20,875 --> 00:00:25,375
CueDeck has two signage modes built specifically for this: Timeline and Programme.

7
00:00:25,675 --> 00:00:28,300
Timeline is a vertical chronological list —

8
00:00:28,600 --> 00:00:31,225
great for lobby screens and corridor monitors.

9
00:00:31,525 --> 00:00:33,775
Programme is a time-by-room grid —

10
00:00:34,075 --> 00:00:38,200
the kind of grid you'd see on a large conference board.

11
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:43,000
Both update in realtime as your sessions go live, overrun, or end.

12
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:46,675
Let me walk you through setting them both up.

13
00:00:46,975 --> 00:00:50,725
Signage is managed from the Signage panel in CueDeck —

14
00:00:51,025 --> 00:00:53,025
accessible from the left sidebar.

15
00:00:53,325 --> 00:00:56,700
Each display you've configured shows here as a card:

16
00:00:56,1000 --> 00:00:59,250
its name, zone type, orientation, and

17
00:00:59,550 --> 00:01:01,550
the current content mode.

18
00:01:01,850 --> 00:01:04,850
If you haven't set up any displays yet,

19
00:01:05,150 --> 00:01:08,150
there's an Add Display button at the top.

20
00:01:08,450 --> 00:01:12,200
Each display corresponds to a physical screen somewhere in your

21
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:16,1000
venue — a lobby monitor, a stage confidence screen, a hallway TV.

22
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:21,050
For today's episode, I already have a few displays configured.

23
00:01:21,350 --> 00:01:23,600
We'll edit two of them —

24
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:26,525
one for Timeline and one for Programme.

25
00:01:26,825 --> 00:01:29,450
To set a display to Timeline mode,

26
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:32,375
open it in the Signage panel and

27
00:01:32,675 --> 00:01:34,925
set the Content Mode to Timeline.

28
00:01:35,225 --> 00:01:37,225
That's it — one dropdown.

29
00:01:37,525 --> 00:01:40,150
But there are two options worth understanding:

30
00:01:40,450 --> 00:01:42,450
scroll style and paginate.

31
00:01:42,750 --> 00:01:46,500
Scroll means the list animates continuously from bottom to top

32
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:49,050
— like a news ticker, but

33
00:01:49,350 --> 00:01:51,350
for your conference schedule.

34
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:55,400
This is ideal for a screen that's visible from a

35
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:59,075
distance and people are glancing at while walking past.

36
00:01:59,375 --> 00:02:01,1000
It's always moving, always showing new content.

37
00:02:02,300 --> 00:02:06,050
Paginate means the list shows a full page of sessions,

38
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:09,350
holds for a set number of seconds —

39
00:02:09,650 --> 00:02:12,275
you configure this, typically between eight and

40
00:02:12,575 --> 00:02:16,325
fifteen seconds — and then advances to the next page.

41
00:02:16,625 --> 00:02:19,250
This is better for a screen where

42
00:02:19,550 --> 00:02:23,300
people are standing and reading, because the content stays still

43
00:02:23,600 --> 00:02:25,850
long enough to be read properly.

44
00:02:26,150 --> 00:02:28,400
I'll set this one to Paginate,

45
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:31,325
ten seconds per page, and save it.

46
00:02:31,625 --> 00:02:33,875
Here's what the display looks like.

47
00:02:34,175 --> 00:02:37,925
Timeline mode renders a vertical chronological list of all sessions

48
00:02:38,225 --> 00:02:41,225
for the day — time on the left,

49
00:02:41,525 --> 00:02:44,150
session title and room on the right.

50
00:02:44,450 --> 00:02:47,450
The LIVE session has a green indicator —

51
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:52,250
it stands out immediately on a dark screen from across a lobby.

52
00:02:52,550 --> 00:02:55,550
Sessions that have already ended are visually dimmed,

53
00:02:55,850 --> 00:02:59,600
so the focus naturally falls on what's current and upcoming.

54
00:02:59,900 --> 00:03:02,150
Future sessions are at full brightness.

55
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:04,450
This updates in realtime.

56
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:08,125
When a director hits Go Live in the console,

57
00:03:08,425 --> 00:03:12,175
that session's status on this screen changes within a second

58
00:03:12,475 --> 00:03:14,475
— no refresh, no delay.

59
00:03:14,775 --> 00:03:17,775
A lobby screen running Timeline is always accurate.

60
00:03:18,075 --> 00:03:20,325
Now let's set up Programme mode.

61
00:03:20,625 --> 00:03:22,875
Same process — open the display,

62
00:03:23,175 --> 00:03:25,800
set the Content Mode dropdown to Programme.

63
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:28,350
Where Timeline is a vertical list,

64
00:03:28,650 --> 00:03:32,400
Programme renders as a grid: time slots run down the

65
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:35,325
left side, rooms run across the top.

66
00:03:35,625 --> 00:03:39,375
Each cell in the grid shows the session in that

67
00:03:39,675 --> 00:03:41,675
room at that time.

68
00:03:41,975 --> 00:03:45,350
It reads exactly like the printed conference programme that

69
00:03:45,650 --> 00:03:47,650
delegates pick up at registration.

70
00:03:47,950 --> 00:03:51,700
This is the mode you want on a large-format screen

71
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
— a wide television in the main lobby,

72
00:03:55,300 --> 00:03:57,550
a display at the registration desk,

73
00:03:57,850 --> 00:04:01,600
or a screen at the entrance to the session floor

74
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:05,275
where people are choosing which room to go to.

75
00:04:05,575 --> 00:04:07,575
Here's the Programme grid.

76
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:10,500
Rooms across the top — Hall A,

77
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:13,050
Hall B, Workshop Room, Breakout —

78
00:04:13,350 --> 00:04:15,600
and time slots down the left.

79
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:18,525
Each session sits in the correct cell.

80
00:04:18,825 --> 00:04:22,950
The currently LIVE session has a green highlight in its cell.

81
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:26,250
As sessions end and new ones go live,

82
00:04:26,550 --> 00:04:28,550
the grid updates automatically.

83
00:04:28,850 --> 00:04:32,600
You can also configure the paginate setting for Programme mode,

84
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:34,900
exactly the same as Timeline.

85
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:38,200
If you have a very large conference —

86
00:04:38,500 --> 00:04:42,250
a lot of rooms, a lot of time slots —

87
00:04:42,550 --> 00:04:45,550
the grid might not fit on one screen,

88
00:04:45,850 --> 00:04:49,225
so you configure pages with an automatic advance interval.

89
00:04:49,525 --> 00:04:52,900
For most single-day conferences with three to five rooms,

90
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:57,700
the Programme grid fits comfortably on a 55-inch screen in landscape orientation.

91
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,625
Quick comparison so the difference is clear.

92
00:05:00,925 --> 00:05:03,175
Scroll is best for: lobby corridors,

93
00:05:03,475 --> 00:05:06,100
anywhere screens are glanced at while moving,

94
00:05:06,400 --> 00:05:09,400
long session lists that would take multiple pages.

95
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:11,950
Paginate is best for: screens where

96
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:14,875
people stop to read, registration desk displays,

97
00:05:15,175 --> 00:05:17,175
anywhere the audience is stationary.

98
00:05:17,475 --> 00:05:21,225
The paginate interval — how many seconds per page —

99
00:05:21,525 --> 00:05:23,525
is set per display.

100
00:05:23,825 --> 00:05:26,825
You can tune it independently for each screen.

101
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:30,500
A large lobby screen might flip every twelve seconds.

102
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:34,550
A registration desk screen might sit for twenty seconds because

103
00:05:34,850 --> 00:05:37,475
delegates are standing there reading every line.

104
00:05:37,775 --> 00:05:40,400
Both settings are saved per display and

105
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:42,950
persist across sessions and page refreshes.

106
00:05:43,250 --> 00:05:45,250
This is worth seeing live.

107
00:05:45,550 --> 00:05:47,800
On the left, the director console.

108
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:50,350
On the right, the Timeline display.

109
00:05:50,650 --> 00:05:54,025
I'll click Go Live on the next session —

110
00:05:54,325 --> 00:05:56,950
and watch what happens on the display.

111
00:05:57,250 --> 00:06:00,250
The session immediately gets a green LIVE badge.

112
00:06:00,550 --> 00:06:02,800
The previous session dims to ENDED.

113
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:05,100
The whole list reflows.

114
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:09,150
All of this happens via a Supabase realtime subscription —

115
00:06:09,450 --> 00:06:13,200
the display page is listening for postgres changes on the

116
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:17,250
session table and re-renders as soon as any status changes.

117
00:06:17,550 --> 00:06:22,050
Your venue's displays are always showing the current state of the event.

118
00:06:22,350 --> 00:06:24,350
Timeline for corridors and lobbies.

119
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:27,275
Programme for overview screens and registration areas.

120
00:06:27,575 --> 00:06:30,200
Both update live, both support scroll and

121
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:35,000
paginate, both are configured from the Signage panel in under a minute.

122
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:40,175
In the next episode, the final piece of the signage system: sponsor logos.

123
00:06:40,475 --> 00:06:42,725
How to upload your sponsor branding,

124
00:06:43,025 --> 00:06:46,400
configure rotation timing, and build a display sequence that

125
00:06:46,700 --> 00:06:48,950
rotates between the sponsor mode and

126
00:06:49,250 --> 00:06:51,250
the session modes automatically.

127
00:06:51,550 --> 00:06:54,175
That one is short and practical —

128
00:06:54,475 --> 00:06:56,475
I'll see you there.
